# =============================================================================
# Rust port — strategy B: track only our Rust port + behavior-freeze docs.
# RPCS3 upstream source ignored (kept locally as reference snapshot).
# =============================================================================
/rpcs3/
/3rdparty/
/Utilities/
/bin/
/buildfiles/
/darwin/
/build-rust-smoke/
/build-rust-debug/

# Rust build artifacts
**/target/
**/Cargo.lock.bak

# Misc upstream files we don't author
/git-clang-format
/objdump.cpp
/pre-commit.readme
/rpcs3.sln
/usertype.dat
/CMakeLists.txt
/CMakePresets.json
/BUILDING.md
/README-rpcs3-upstream.md
/.cargo/
/.ci/
/.clang-format
/.clangd
/.editorconfig
/.gdbinit
/.github/
/.gitmodules

# Local tooling state (not part of repo)
/.claude/
/.serena/
**/.claude/
**/.serena/
**/*.local.json

# Python bytecode (never tracked)
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Local backup files (never tracked)
*.bak
*.bak-*

# PS3 firmware / commercial blobs (never tracked — sourced separately by users)
*.PUP
*.pup

# Behavior-freeze SPU homebrew build artifacts.
# CC0 sources + Makefile + capture script are tracked under
# behavior-freeze/fixtures/spu/sources/<homebrew>/; binary outputs
# (`*.elf`, `*.self`, intermediate `.bin`/`.s`/`.o`) are reproducible
# via `make` and stay untracked. The captured trace + `.spuimg`
# side-file under behavior-freeze/fixtures/spu/{traces,images}/ ARE
# the load-bearing artifacts and DO get committed.
behavior-freeze/fixtures/spu/sources/*/build/
behavior-freeze/fixtures/spu/sources/*/spu/*.elf
behavior-freeze/fixtures/spu/sources/*/*_bin.s
behavior-freeze/fixtures/spu/sources/*/*_bin.o
behavior-freeze/fixtures/spu/sources/*/*.bin

